Rating: 4
I've been making this recipe for well over a year and tailor it depending upon what's on hand - a few things I do - don't use the entire amount of oil, but substitute walnut oil- you can always thin with a little more vinegr or water. Also, I use grade B maple syrup - it's the darker version, adds a depth of flavor - for our tastes the extra sugar is not needed. Also try using a mixture of Cherries and other dried berries. Sam's Club has a dried Cherry Berry mix that is awesome and then I omit the apple altogether. Alittle feta cheese added counterbalances the sweetness nicely also. My father in law who is south side chicago polish - likes plain basic food loves this salad. He always takes seconds!!

