(First review didn't get through) Made this salad again for a big birthday dinner - always a hit! A few random thoughts... I've used Craisins in the past; tried dried cherries this time and liked them a bit better. Didn't peel the apples; chopped them instead of cutting into matchsticks. Toasted the chopped nuts for about 5 min. in a 350 oven, just till they got fragrant. Omitted sugar in the dressing and used only half the dressing on the salad. Tossed the cherries in a small amount of dressing before putting them on the salad - helped keep them from sinking to the bottom right away. Chopped up some leftover chicken a couple days later and threw it on top of the salad for a main dish - my picky kids loved it! (Made a new salad...leftover salad would have been too soggy!)

