Rating: 4
Delicious!!!! Well-liked even by picky children. Added blue cheese and spiced the walnuts (toast walnuts in pan, then when they are almost tosted, add a small pat of butter, a touch of brown sugar, and old bay seasoning, or any season salt to the walnuts and stir to coat). Just be careful, if everyone starts nibbling on the spiced walnuts, they may be gone before dinner. I also used balsamic vinegar to give it more of a kick. I suggest serving the dressing and ingredients in small bowls on the table, so that everyone can put the exact amount of ingredients/dressing that they like on their individual salad!

