Rating: 3
Nice winter salad--flavors really complimented each other. Left out apples (ran out of time) and used cranberries instead of cherries. Suggest crushing nuts well, chopping up cranberries* and mixing with 1/4 cup of dressing. Add this to salad and toss to coat. Leave remainder of dressing on table for guests to add to salad as needed. *Chopping the nuts and berries into smaller pieces will make them lighter and allow them--once coated with dressing--to stick to the lettuce instead of sinking to the bottom of the salad.

