To me this sounded disgusting, but I decided to try it anyway. Big mistake! I've tossed quite a few salads in my day, and never, EVER, did it occur to me to use this combination of ingredients. Mayo? Apples? Nuts? Cherries? Why not just toss together some moldy crutons, cigarette butts and lemon wedges drizzled in used coffee ground vinegrette? I offered the leftovers to the homeless man that lives downstairs but he refused it. Poor man. If you really want what I call "salad," try this little recipe. Lettuce, vinegar. That's it. Best recipe for salad that I know. Sure, it's not "fancy schmansy" like one you'll fine on this web site, but it blows them all away.

